{"parentUuid":"4a45e903-b5ea-4a5a-8b6d-093b6af221d4","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01MPtyrFnaHdaEvd4LGx53K5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 🎯 Migração Complianz dev→prod CONCLUÍDA\n\n| Local | banner | accept | deny | scripts | Status |\n|-------|--------|--------|------|--------:|--------|\n| **Blog 1 raiz** (`/`) | ✅ true | ACEITAR | REJEITAR | 1 | ✅ |\n| **Blog 2 cultura** (`/cultura/`) | ✅ true | (loaded via JS) | (loaded via JS) | 1 | ✅ |\n| **Blog 2 Atlas** | ✅ true | (loaded via JS) | (loaded via JS) | 1 | ✅ |\n| **Blog 1 EN** (`/en/`) | ❌ false | — | — | 0 | ⚠️ WPML lang-specific |\n\nConsole mostra `[LOG] opt-in @ complianz.min.js` → plugin inicializou em modo opt-in (LGPD correto). Aviso `Fallback default css file used` é cosmético — você precisa entrar no admin Complianz e clicar \"Save\" no Banner Settings pra remover.\n\n**Pendências:**\n1. ⚠️ **Blog 1 EN** (`/en/`) sem banner — provavelmente WPML language-specific (Complianz vê EN como outra \"região\"). Investigação separada\n2. ⚠️ Banner usa CSS default (não custom) em prod — clicar \"Save\" no admin Complianz banner settings\n\n## Commit do script + bundles"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3094,"cache_read_input_tokens":951668,"output_tokens":1261,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3094,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1261,"cache_read_input_tokens":951668,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3094},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cad3F6zgx3q9xMJpgmGR1","type":"assistant","uuid":"e6c425a7-f70d-476c-9057-2a6217d87d5a","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:34:07.769Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao","sessionId":"55811d4e-34d6-42df-9582-284664a6a576","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main","slug":"prepare-o-deploy-do-snappy-taco"}
{"parentUuid":"e6c425a7-f70d-476c-9057-2a6217d87d5a","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01MPtyrFnaHdaEvd4LGx53K5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KLy9PAKmtTjVnqxBr8o4Ps","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2\ngit add docker-dev/common/scripts/cmplz-migrate-dev-to-prod.sh\ngit commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfeat(scripts): cmplz-migrate-dev-to-prod.sh — migra Complianz dev→prod multisite\n\nPlugin Complianz Network Active exige config separada por blog.\nWizard manual e tedioso e propenso a divergencia. Este script\nexporta wp_options + wp_2_options de DEV (source-of-truth) e\nimporta em PROD via SSH+wp-cli, idempotente.\n\nSteps:\n1. Backup PROD: dump opcoes Complianz blog 1 + blog 2 (download local)\n2. Export DEV: snapshot todas opcoes cmplz_*/complianz_* dos 2 blogs\n3. Skip per-blog tracking (cmplz_activation_time, cmplz_wsc_*, etc)\n4. Import PROD via wp eval com base64+serialize\n5. Validacao smoke pos-migracao (curl HTML)\n\nNOTA: este commit reflete o script mas a aplicacao real foi feita via\nloop bash inline (script tinha bug de stdin consumption). Refatoracao\nusa estrategia BUNDLE: criar 1 JSON com todas as opts, scp pro prod,\n1 unica chamada wp eval pra importar todas.\n\nResultado em prod (2026-05-02):\n- Blog 1: 73 keys cmplz_options (country=BR, consent=optin, ads=yes)\n- Blog 2: 73 keys cmplz_options (idem)\n- Banner aparece em / e /cultura/ + sub-paths\n- /en/ ainda sem banner (WPML lang-specific, investigacao separada)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"\n\ngit push origin main 2>&1 | tail -3","description":"Commit migration script"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3094,"cache_read_input_tokens":951668,"output_tokens":1261,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3094,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1261,"cache_read_input_tokens":951668,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3094},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cad3F6zgx3q9xMJpgmGR1","type":"assistant","uuid":"5a96ac20-e671-457b-a88e-0b26929e98b9","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:34:20.295Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao","sessionId":"55811d4e-34d6-42df-9582-284664a6a576","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main","slug":"prepare-o-deploy-do-snappy-taco"}
