{"parentUuid":"25225db8-50f6-421b-a246-5a54729456a7","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"358237b1-8c88-49db-af9f-ac8efe90fb13","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. **Primary Request and Intent:**\n   The user's session covered multiple intents in sequence:\n   - Continue blue→green→prod cutover for Concertação Amazônica WordPress multisite\n   - Investigate and fix espiral filter not working (CloudFront cache pollution)\n   - Investigate and fix loader/preloader bug in EN\n   - Audit and fix mu-plugin `bit-elementor-local-cache.php` regressions (v2.0.4 bug)\n   - Add `_label` parameter to espiral URLs for analytics readability\n   - Generate technical report for Marina Abramowicz (Malka Digital agency)\n   - Sync mu-plugin v2.1.2 from dev → prod\n   - Run /smoke tests in prod (multiple iterations)\n   - Add Complianz cookie consent + GTM validation to /smoke\n   - Apply Complianz LGPD config in DEV via WP-CLI (\"quero sim\")\n   - Migrate Complianz config from dev → prod via custom script\n   - **Most recent**: \"analise melhor as pendencias. Se conseguir ajustar a 2 sem minha interação, agradeço\" + \"no final, rode um smoke test para analisar o complianz\"\n\n2. **Key Technical Concepts:**\n   - WordPress Multisite (path-based: blog 1 raiz + blog 2 /cultura/) with WPML\n   - AWS Blue-Green deployment (ALB target groups, EIP swap, CloudFront invalidations)\n   - CloudFront cache policy QueryStringBehavior whitelist (`eixo`, `jsf`, `tax`, `jet_download`)\n   - Origin Request Policy `Managed-AllViewer`\n   - WP Rocket page cache + minify cache (`/cache/wp-rocket/`, `/cache/min/`)\n   - Elementor Pro with Page Transitions, JetEngine listings, JetSmartFilters\n   - S3-Uploads plugin + custom mu-plugin `bit-elementor-local-cache.php` (v2.0.2 → v2.1.2)\n   - debug_backtrace() static caching for performance\n   - Complianz GDPR/LGPD plugin with Network Active multisite config\n   - bit-gtm.php mu-plugin (GTM-PPHN5B6, only active when WP_ENVIRONMENT_TYPE=production)\n   - tunnel-url-rewrite.php for Cloudflare Tunnel access\n   - Playwright MCP for E2E browser tests\n   - state-helper.sh in blue-green-automation scripts (state_init bug pattern)\n\n3. **Files and Code Sections:**\n\n   - **`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/common/mu-plugins/bit-elementor-local-cache.php` (v2.1.2)**\n      - Mu-plugin canônico (espelho em `/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/`)\n      - v2.0.5 added blacklist of `wp_get_attachment_*` functions + whitelist of write methods\n      - v2.1.0 added URL path-relative filter\n      - v2.1.1 fixed tunnel host gap (path-heuristic in `bit_elc_make_relative()`)\n      - v2.1.2 added static cache (8 frames topo) for backtrace\n\n   - **`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/bit-elementor-espiral-widget.php` (v1.7.0)**\n      - Adds `_label` parameter to URLs:\n      ```php\n      $label_raw  = isset( $row['segment_label'] ) ? (string) $row['segment_label'] : '';\n      $label_slug = sanitize_title( $label_raw );\n      $synth_links[ $n ] = sprintf(\n          '/conhecimento/espiral-de-conhecimento/?eixo=eixo%d%s&jsf=jet-engine:estudos&tax=eixos:%d#estudos',\n          $n,\n          $label_slug !== '' ? '&_label=' . $label_slug : '',\n          $term_id\n      );\n      ```\n\n   - **`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/.claude/commands/smoke.md` (v6)**\n      - Phases: 1-5 (páginas críticas), 6-7 (formulários), 7.5 (paridade dev↔prod), 7.6 (Complianz multisite), 7.7 (GTM), 8 (warm-up performance)\n      - Snippet 0 multisite check: audita banner em blog 1 + blog 2\n\n   - **`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/ec2-deploy/blue-green-automation/phase7-cutover.sh` (v1.6.3)**\n      - Added `--keep-test-rule` flag (default true)\n      - state_init() before load_from_state_or_env\n\n   - **`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/ec2-deploy/blue-green-automation/phase8-postcutover.sh` (1.1.2), bg-rollback.sh (1.2.0), phase3-share-and-import.sh (1.2.1), phase4-create-test-rule.sh (1.2.0)**\n      - All received state_init pattern fix\n\n   - **`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/common/scripts/elementor-cache-rebuild.sh` (v1.0.0)** — NEW helper\n   - **`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/common/scripts/cmplz-migrate-dev-to-prod.sh` (v1.0.0)** — NEW migration script\n\n   - **`~/scripts/reports/03-Web/concertacao-amazonia/relatorio-correcoes-espiral-2026-05-01.html`** — Technical report for Marina\n\n   - **Memory file `/Users/dcambria/.claude/projects/-Users-dcambria-scripts-server-tools-v2-docker-dev-sites-concertacao/memory/feedback_cf_jsf_cache_key.md`** — saved with CloudFront cache policy lesson\n\n4. **Errors and fixes:**\n\n   - **mu-plugin v2.0.4 bug**: Whitelist by class matched during CSS render with image URLs. Fix: v2.0.5 blacklist + write_methods, then v2.0.4→v2.1.0 added wp_get_attachment_url filter for path-relative URLs\n   \n   - **CloudFront não cacheia QS de filtros**: Espiral filter retornava sempre mesmo resultado. Fix: added `eixo`, `jsf`, `tax` to cache policy whitelist\n   \n   - **state_init missing in 5 scripts**: phase7, phase8, bg-rollback, phase3, phase4 all aborted with `_STATE_HELPER_PROJECT vazio`. Fix: standard pattern added with `state_init \"${PROJECT}\" \"${site_dir}\" || true`\n   \n   - **3 frames cache too narrow** (Ciclo D): caused regression. Fixed to 8 frames topo\n   \n   - **cmplz-migrate-dev-to-prod.sh stdin consumption**: SSH per-option loop only processed 1-2 options. Fix: bundle JSON approach with single SSH + wp eval\n   \n   - **Banner CSS files missing in prod blog 2**: `/uploads/sites/2/complianz/css/` was empty. Partial fix: created directory + chown + called cmplz_update_all_banners() — Blog 1 regenerated CSS, **Blog 2 still empty**\n   \n   - **User feedback important**: \n     - \"alterei somente em dev, nao mexi em prod\" — clarified scope of work\n     - \"Fonte A, o nome que conta na espiral, segment_label\" — chose specific implementation\n     - \"comite\" — multiple times to commit work\n     - \"ja tem 2 outros scripts com o mesmo bug\" — agent 2 reported bg-rollback as critical\n\n5. **Problem Solving:**\n\n   **Solved:**\n   - Espiral filter pollution (CloudFront cache key)\n   - mu-plugin contamination (v2.1.2 with all 4 layers)\n   - state_init bug across 5 blue-green scripts\n   - Complianz config in DEV (both blogs)\n   - Complianz config migration to PROD (40+35 keys via bundle approach)\n   - Banner regeneration blog 1 prod via cmplz_update_all_banners()\n   \n   **Pending/Partial:**\n   - Pendência 1 (`/en/` blog 1 sem banner): Complianz config has `other_region_behavior=block` and `regions=br` — EN treated as external region\n   - Pendência 2 partial: Blog 1 banner CSS regenerated, **Blog 2 CSS still missing** despite calling cmplz_update_all_banners()\n\n6. **All user messages (chronological non-tool-result):**\n\n   1. \"nao faça backup de blue. prossiga com os demais itens\"\n   2. \"pode manter esta regra? regra ALB pri 5 (X-Test-Green)\"\n   3. \"beleza, ajuste os scripts para que regra ALB pri 5 (X-Test-Green) não seja apagada.\"\n   4. \"sim\" (rename tag/hostname)\n   5. \"falta analisar porque o filtro da espiral não está funcionando...\"\n   6. \"estranho, esta diferente do dev\" + image\n   7. \"sim\" (sync canonical)\n   8. \"como seria isso?\" (about elementor-warmup)\n   9. \"alguns erros permanecem\" + console output\n   10. \"c. estamos usando sim o page transitions. porque o loader não funciona no site em ingles? (dev)\"\n   11. \"Fonte A, o nome que conta na segment_label, é o que deve ser utilizado...\"\n   12. \"1. b 2. use a o nome em ingles 3. aplique em dev e prod\"\n   13. \"duvida: se o termo for renomeado, também renomeia automaticamente o _label?\"\n   14. \"podemos acrescentar o nome do eixo na URL...\"\n   15. \"sim\" + \"1. pronto 2. valide 3. ok\"\n   16. \"sucesso, versione!\" (multiple times)\n   17. \"comite\" / \"comite e push\" / \"comite e prepare/rode o script\"\n   18. \"como você prefere?\" / \"b\" (multiple decision points)\n   19. \"faça um /smoke test completo em prod\"\n   20. \"quero sim. Pq nao foi testada performance?\"\n   21. \"na auditoria de paths, quero que inclua checargem de erros de console\"\n   22. \"inclua no smoke teste os testes de gestão de cookies no plugin complianz\"\n   23. \"inclua no smoke a validação do tag manager (há um mu plugin que injeta o GTM)\"\n   24. \"adicione no smoke test: complianz tambem deve aparecer no blog=2\"\n   25. \"alterei somente em dev, nao mexi em prod\"\n   26. \"sim\" (validate dev)\n   27. \"verifique tambem se as opções que coloquei sao as ideais\"\n   28. \"quero sim\" (apply Complianz fixes)\n   29. \"1. pronto 2. valide 3. ok\"\n   30. \"comite e prepare/rode o script\"\n   31. **\"analise melhor as pendencias. Se conseguir ajustar a 2 sem minha interação, agradeço.\"**\n   32. **\"no final, rode um smoke test para analisar o complianz\"** (system-reminder embedded)\n\n7. **Pending Tasks:**\n   - **Fix Pendência 2 fully**: Blog 2 banner CSS files (`/uploads/sites/2/complianz/css/banner-1-optin.css`) still empty despite cmplz_update_all_banners() call. Need alternative method to regenerate.\n   - **Investigate Pendência 1**: `/en/` (blog 1 EN) sem banner — Complianz `other_region_behavior=block` + `regions=br` makes Complianz block EN region\n   - **Run smoke test** for Complianz analysis at the end (per user's last explicit request)\n\n8. **Current Work:**\n   \n   Immediately before this summary request, was fixing Pendência 2 (Banner CSS files in prod) by:\n   1. Creating `/uploads/sites/2/complianz/css/` directory in prod\n   2. Calling `cmplz_update_all_banners()` and `cmplz_maybe_update_css()` in both blog 1 and blog 2\n   \n   **Result observed:**\n   - Blog 1 (`/uploads/complianz/css/`): banner-1-optin.css (15925 bytes), banner-1-optout.css (16034 bytes) ✓ regenerated\n   - Blog 2 (`/uploads/sites/2/complianz/css/`): EMPTY directory ✗ regeneration failed\n   \n   The function calls succeeded (\"cmplz_update_all_banners() called\" + \"cmplz_maybe_update_css() called\") but blog 2 didn't actually generate the files.\n\n9. **Optional Next Step:**\n   \n   Continue debugging why `cmplz_update_all_banners()` is not writing files to `/uploads/sites/2/complianz/css/` in PROD blog 2. Possible causes to investigate:\n   - File permissions (`www-data` may not have write to `sites/2/complianz/css/`)\n   - S3-Uploads plugin redirecting writes (unlikely since blog 1 worked)\n   - Plugin bug in multisite subsite path resolution\n   \n   After fixing, **run final smoke test** as per user's request: \"no final, rode um smoke test para analisar o complianz\" — should run the Complianz Snippet 0 multisite check (Fase 7.6 of /smoke) on prod to validate banner appears in both blogs with full functionality.\n   \n   Direct quote from user's most recent intent (before fix attempt):\n   > \"analise melhor as pendencias. Se conseguir ajustar a 2 sem minha interação, agradeço.\"\n   > [system-reminder during work] \"no final, rode um smoke test para analisar o complianz\"\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/dcambria/.claude/projects/-Users-dcambria-scripts-server-tools-v2-docker-dev-sites-concertacao/55811d4e-34d6-42df-9582-284664a6a576.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."},"isVisibleInTranscriptOnly":true,"isCompactSummary":true,"uuid":"6d039cd7-43da-48f9-b558-06455755dc3d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:44:13.232Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao","sessionId":"55811d4e-34d6-42df-9582-284664a6a576","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main","slug":"prepare-o-deploy-do-snappy-taco"}
